INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(59002, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My pack and I are too weak to oppose the dark forces on this island.\n\nWe will use the last of our strength to grant you our power.\n\nUse it to rid the island of the ogres\' necromancy.\n\nFree the countless souls they have trapped here.', 45745), -- A Shaman's Duty
(59254, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fine work, $n. Let\'s speak with Alaria and hunt down those quilboar.', 45745), -- Enhanced Combat Tactics
(62704, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your choice is made. The Purpose will guide you forward.', 45745), -- The Threads of Fate
(29599, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done a great thing, $n. Alas, the young warchief\'s memory of these events must be as they originally were...', 45745), -- Escape from Durnholde
(29598, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are friends of Taretha? So this is her new plan? Very well then...', 45745), -- Taretha's Diversion
(26907, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well this day. Charlga\'s advisors are as much a threat as any.', 45338), -- Take Them Down!
(26901, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done! This is just what we need, $n.', 45338), -- Going, Going, Guano!
(26905, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Take this gift. You have earned my blessing this day.', 45338), -- Agamaggan's Charge
(26906, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Spirit of Agamaggan looks at you. An ancient voice echoes inside your head.>$B$BI\'ve been waiting for you to come here.', 45338), -- Agamaggan
(27698, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Without her powerful servants, Princess Theradras is significantly more vulnerable. Find her lair, $n...it is time to strike.$B$B<You feel a sizable lump of gold appear in your bags, clearly a reward for your work here.>', 45745), -- Servants of Theradras
(27185, 275, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nicely done, lad! Without them new weapons, they\'re just as easy t\' kill as they were when they were alive!', 45338), -- Cutting the Competition
(27223, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You may have this as a suitable reward. I found it nestled in the armor of one of the scourge here.', 45338), -- Retribution
(27208, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s good we stopped Balnazzar now. Before long, his army would have overtaken all of Stratholme, giving him a powerful center for his new unholy empire.', 45338), -- The Dreadlord Balnazzar
(27305, 378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Master Fordring will be glad beyond measure to see this painting again.', 45338), -- Of Love and Family
(27676, 71, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fantastic! Great work! We\'ll know all that Dig Three has to tell us in no time at all!', 45338), -- Behind Closed Doors
(27673, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is incredible, $n. The power coursing through each core...the contrasting powers so close together!$B$BI\'ll take this to the proper dwarves right away. These cores are extremely important!', 45338), -- It's What's Inside That Counts
(27677, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, lad! Now go to the discs and learn all you can!', 45338), -- Archaedas, The Ancient Stone Watcher
(27672, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Don\'t worry about the chamber, my boys will check it out! You have more important things to do!', 45338), -- The Chamber of Khaz'mul
(66650, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You are ready. As the air changes ever so slightly, you reach out and close your hand. Within seconds, you feel it appear. You don\'t look for your prize this time, the two of you exist in perfect harmony.>', 45338), -- Fate's Finale
(66649, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Once again, you are met with something you do not understand. This time you do not question why. The journey has been its own reward. This is merely a means to remember it.>', 45338), -- Turning the Wheel
(61100, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your assistance to our cause has not gone unnoticed. More and more venthyr across the realm bind themselves to the Court of Harvesters instead of the Master. \n\nPlease accept these token of gratitude.', 45114), -- Supplies from the Court of Harvesters
(49135, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With these sigils, the Vindicaar can bypass the Burning Throne\'s defenses.$b$bThe time has come to press our advantage and end this war.', 45114), -- Antorus, the Burning Throne: The Heart of Argus
(59970, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our bargain has been struck.\n\nCall upon me from the Void, and I will answer.\n\n<The voidwalker looks at the goblin\'s corpse.>\n\nLet us see if you are stronger than those who came before you.', 45114), -- A Warlock's Bargain
(59947, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good to see you all back in one piece. You are testament to the Horde\'s strength of will!\n\nLet\'s hope Gloomburst is as powerful as he is unhinged.', 45114), -- Message to Base
(59944, 4, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks for the save! They must be desperate for sacrifices if they wanted to use someone who\'s already dead.\n\nIf anyone is going to drain my life essence to use in a forbidden ritual, it\'s going to be me!', 45114), -- The Rescue of Herbert Gloomburst
(59945, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The harpies seem to be retreating to their roost. That should give us time to stop the ogres.', 45114), -- Harpy Culling
(59946, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The harpies grow weaker with their totems destroyed. Let us hope they realize that the Horde is a force to be reckoned with.', 45114), -- Purge the Totems
(59943, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have found the missing member of the expedition... but we have many problems to deal with first.', 45114), -- The Harpy Problem
(59949, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Crenna Earth-Daughter will be vital to our cause. Her connection to nature will help us understand what the ogres have done to this island.\n\nGood work, recruit.', 45114), -- Who Lurks in the Pit
(59948, 1, 6, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A giant pit filled with necrotic energy and spiders.\n\nI used to hate spiders. Now that I\'m Forsaken, I don\'t think they\'re all that bad.\n\nThey will still definitely kill you, though.', 45114), -- Westward Bound
(59950, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope you have what you need. \n\nThrog found this bag nearby and thought you might have use of it.', 45114), -- Stocking Up on Supplies
(59942, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, stranger. I failed the Horde... I was not strong enough to stop this threat on my own.', 45114), -- The Re-Deather
(59941, 397, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So the giant boar was a fool\'s errand, and you turned the device into a weapon instead?\n\nGood work. Let\'s see if you can pull this off.', 45114), -- Re-sizing the Situation
(59940, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'All right, time to bend some rules and make a giant boar!', 45114), -- The Choppy Booster Mk. 5
(59939, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A fine job. The quilboar seem to be keeping their distance. Perhaps they learned their lesson.', 45114), -- Forbidden Quilboar Necromancy
(59938, 4, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You sure got some guts! I respect that. I joined this expedition thinkin\' it\'d be a quick and easy way to make a little profit.\n\nBut now with all this necromancy and crazy ogres... maybe I can make a LOT of profit!', 45114), -- Down with the Quilboar
(59935, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have good news... and most unfortunate news.', 45114), -- Northbound
(59933, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re ready to slaughter the quilboar! Let\'s speak to Won\'sa and see what she knows.', 45114), -- Enhanced Combat Tactics
(59932, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Won\'sa quickly eats the meat that you cooked.>\n\nLooks I not gonna be knockin\' on Bwonsamdi\'s door, after all.\n\nYa best hurry. Da quilboar took Shuja and da rest of da expedition!', 45114), -- Cooking Meat
(59931, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So... hungry...\n\nDey took... everyone else... I be... da last one...', 45114), -- Finding the Lost Expedition
(59930, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re back on our feet. Now let\'s move. The lost expedition is somewhere on this island.', 45114), -- Emergency First Aid
(59929, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work. Let\'s get the survivors back on their feet.', 45114), -- Murloc Mania
(66661, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That coin... no one in Oribos will take its kind, and I doubt you\'d survive the trip to the market that could. If I may be so bold, perhaps my associates and I could provide assistance?', 45114), -- It's Just a Coin, What Could it Cost?
(51421, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome ta Tiragarde, boss-mon. Ya ready to be parleyin\'?', 45745), -- Shiver Me Timbers
(51803, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have the Queen\'s trust. For now.', 45745), -- The Kul Tiras Campaign
(51800, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You have chosen to set sail for Tiragarde Sound.>', 45745), -- Foothold: Tiragarde Sound
(52749, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re here.', 45745), -- The War Campaign
(47512, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The swamp of Nazmir represents the largest threat to my people. I am glad you chose to help me in this.', 45745), -- Nazmir
(46931, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My father believes he is indulging me. He has ruled for two hundred years, many lifetimes of trolls. In his mind, de threats dat face our kingdom are minor.\n\nI have seen too much to believe dat.\n\nSo since my father and his advisors would not help, I turned to someone who would.\n\nYour warchief needs our fleet, and I need her champions. I have a battle plan here on what to do.\n\nChoose your first move. If de Horde helps my people, den I will help de Horde.', 45745), -- Speaker of the Horde
(46930, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your deeds had reached my ears before your feet ever set foot in my land. It is time we spoke.', 45745), -- Rastakhan
(46957, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dat is far enough, Horde scum.', 45745); -- Welcome to Zuldazar
